

Now we will learn how to push our images in Amazon ECR (Elastic Container Repository)

1. Go to the ECR and create the repository. It can be public and private depending on the requirements.

2. Why we are using ECR because in this all the features are free.
      For ex : we can create private repository , we can scan our images for vunlerability etc

3. Now to use the Amazon ECR aws cli package should be installed :
      Link : https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/getting-started-install.html
      
      Open the above link and there you will all the steps required to install aws-cli package

      Steps to install aws-cli :

            a) First install the unzip package : apt-install unzip
            b) curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
               unzip awscliv2.zip
               sudo ./aws/install
            c) After that configure the AWS Credential or AWS IAM role need to be attached
            d) Now create the role in AWS and attach to the EC2 instance
            




